1) make our own travis and edit the .travis.yml file
2) edit bower.json (or make our own)
3) edit package.json (the nodejs file)
4) connect mongolab to heroku ---> https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/getting-started-with-nodejs#provision-a-database


How to run db:
go to mongo/bin
run sudo ./mongod

MongoLab
type
heroku config | grep MONGOLAB_URI
to see the mongolab db url (its an environment variable)

Theres a heroku repo and git repo.
To change stuff on heroku use this command after committing local changes
git push heroku master